Congratulations to Russian Speaker of State Duma 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Choe Thae Bok, chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, sent a congratulatory message to Boris Gryzlov upon his reelection as speaker of the State Duma of the Russian Federal Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished him good health and greater success in his responsible work.

Chinese Ambassador Hosts Receptions 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, Tuesday hosted a reception at the embassy on the occasion of New Year, Juche 97 (2008). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were officials of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea including Secretary Choe Thae Bok and Department Director Jang Song Thaek and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials of the Chinese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the reception, the ambassador said that the Korean people have achieved signal successes in developing the economy and improving the standard of people's living and made progress in the north-south relations and the external relations under the leadership of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will strive to continuously promote the development of the relations between the two parties and the two countries in keeping with the agreement reached by the supreme leaders of China and the DPRK and the common desire of the two peoples, he stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok in his speech referred to the fact that the Chinese people have made great achievements in building a harmonious socialist society based on the principle of people first and governance for the people and the scientific outlook on development under the leadership of the Communist Party of China with Hu Jintao as its General Secretary this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the traditional DPRK-China friendship would further develop by the joint efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, the ambassador hosted receptions for officials of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun and Vice-Minister of the People's Armed Forces Pak Jae Gyong and other officials concerned.

Diamond Jubilee of Korea National Insurance Corporation Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- The Korea National Insurance Corporation celebrated its 60th founding anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past six decades since its foundation in Juche 36 (1947) the corporation has widely organized various kinds of insurance suited to the actual conditions of the country, contributing to putting the production and management of industrial establishments and cooperatives on a normal basis, protecting people's property, expanding the field of insurance and consolidating the socialist insurance system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has become a competent insurance body comprehensively engaged in property insurance, life insurance, reinsurance, information technology and financial investment by conducting brisk activities to raise function and role of insurance in keeping with the present tendency of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting was held Tuesday to mark the diamond jubilee of the corporation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, was among those present at the meeting.

Galas of Youth and Students Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Dancing-parties of youth and students took place across the country on Monday to commemorate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In different parts of Pyongyang, including the plazas of the Tower of the Juche Idea, the Monument to Party Founding and the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium, youth and students merrily danced to the tune of songs with their great joy of holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem and earnest yearning for Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, similar parties of youth and students were held in local cities and provincial and county seats, including Chongjin, Phyongsong, Sariwon and Hamhung cities.

Colorful Events Held across Country 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Art performances and other colorful events were held in various parts of the country to significantly commemorate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Performances were given by artistes of the national art troupes at the theatres and cultural houses in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang high praises of the undying exploits of Kim Jong Il who has led the revolutionary cause of Juche to steady victory and the glorious revolutionary career and feats of Kim Jong Suk who established the noble tradition of devotedly defending the leader and brought about the bright future of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art troupes of Kangwon, North Phyongan and other provinces also gave performances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibitions of flowers of the sun opened in Kim Jong Suk County of Ryanggang Province and Hoeryong City of North Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials and other working people in Jagang Province made study tours of the Insan Revolutionary Battle Site in Rangrim County during which they laid floral baskets and bouquets before the mosaic depicting Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oratorical meetings, presentations of poems and songs and other events were held by working people's organizations in South and North Phyongan Provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art performances and presentations of songs took place at the Kim Chaek Iron and Steel Complex, the Migok Co-op Farm in Sariwon City and other factories, enterprises and farms across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 20,000 working people and members of the women's union in South Hamgyong Province had sports and folk games, a contest in peasants' dances and other colorful events at Hamhung Square.

Kim Jong Suk's Exploits in Building Party and State  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk was the most faithful soldier of President Kim Il Sung. She laid a foundation for the implementation of the President's line of building the Party and the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Everywhere she went, she saw to it that the work of the party organizations was carried out according to the revolutionary idea of the President in the days of the building of a new country when democracy and reaction were standing face to face in sharp antagonism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
She visited the Chongjin City Party Committee in North Hamgyong Province in December Juche 34 (1945) and told officials who were going to great pains for the implementation of the line of building party organizations to firmly build them up with people tested and tempered in the revolutionary struggle for the liberation of the country as the core elements, admit elites to the party from among the masses of various strata and form party organizations in factories and enterprises as early as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And she gave detailed instructions to establish a strict centralized discipline in the Party, raise the role of the propaganda department of the Party, reinforce the ranks of cadres and make officials possess the revolutionary method of work and the popular style of work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
In the later period, she put deviations on the right track in the work of different local party organizations to see that the President's line of Party building was implemented correctly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
She also put her heart and soul into the work for implementing the President's line of building the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A few days after her triumphant return to the homeland, she got together with officials of a local people's committee and told them to carry through the President's line of state building up to the hilt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
When she visited local areas, she acquainted herself with the work of the people's committees and clarified tasks of the officials to give a better account of themselves as intended by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Braving danger, she gave lectures to audiences into which quite a few reactionaries sneaked their way and brought home the justice of the President's line of people's government to the people, inspiring them to turn out as one in the building of a new country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The great changes in the days of the enforcement of the laws on agrarian reform, nationalization of major industries, labor, sex equality, etc. promulgated by the President were associated with the noble feats of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There was no affair which did not bear marks of her efforts in the days of building the state, such as instituting the national emblem and the national flag well reflecting the far-reaching plan and policy of the President on state building and drafting the constitution of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Indeed, the great feats of Kim Jong Suk for the future development of the Workers' Party of Korea and the revolution and for the prosperity of the DPRK will remain long in history.

Kim Jong Suk's Immortal Service for Army Building 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk had keenly experienced from the first days of her revolutionary activities the truth of the revolution that the country and the revolution could be defended only by force of arms, and done her best to bring the line of army-building put forward by President Kim Il Sung into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the national liberation, she assisted the President in the efforts to build a regular army and gave important instructions to officials in this regard on over 420 occasions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She visited the Pyongyang Institute, a base for training military and political cadres, more than 30 times to emphasize that efforts should be exerted to the education of the students in the loyalty to the President. And she also frequented to Central Security Officers School where she amended its teaching program so as to arm the students with the military ideas of the President and tactics suitable to the actual conditions of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She made deep attention to the training of commanding officers of all services in the building of the regular army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One day in June of Juche 35 (1946) she instructed officials of the Pyongyang Institute to construct an airfield with its own efforts and went out to the construction site to give a helping hand to the students and inspire them to complete the project at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And one day in November 1947 she informed the director of Marine Security Officers School of the President's instructions on rearing naval officers by itself and asked leading officials of a relevant province to render a positive helping hand to the work for setting up the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those years she was also busy with efforts to guide the logistic work for the building of a regular army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She found herself among manufacturers of military uniforms and led them to produce the trial uniforms and accoutrements as early as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to her energetic effort, the designs of uniforms of the Korean People's Army were fixed in March 1947. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the first mechanized unit of the regular army was being organized, she made uniforms of commanding officers of a tank unit by herself and called on the unit frequently and paid attention to training tank drivers within three months, breaking the existing formula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal exploits performed by her in the work to strengthen the armed forces of the DPRK as an invincible country will shine long in the Songun revolutionary history.

New Stamps on "Arirang" Issued 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- The DPRK has newly brought out postage stamps (2 kinds of sheetlet) reflecting the grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Printed in the upper part of the sheetlets are the May Day Stadium, the venue of the performance, and the registration mark of the Guinness World Records. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sheetlets compile postage stamps showing in unique way scenes of the Prelude "Arirang", Chapter 1 "Arirang Nation", Chapter 2 "Songun Arirang", Chapter 3 "Arirang of Happiness", Chapter 4 "Arirang of National Reunification" and Finale "Arirang of Prosperous and Powerful Nation".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In last August "Arirang" was registered in the Guinness World Records as the largest gymnastic and artistic performance in the world.

Revolutionary Exploits of Kim Jong Suk Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- The revolutionary exploits performed by anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk will always be remembered by the servicepersons and people of the DPRK. Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in an editorial dedicated to her 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial says: Kim Jong Suk performed undying exploits for the country and the people, the times and history which an ordinary human being could not do even in thousands of years. She set a shining example showing how a revolutionary and a human being should live and struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was an indomitable revolutionary fighter as she created a shining model in devotedly defending the leader with transparent outlook on the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She absolutely trusted President Kim Il Sung, the pioneer of the Korean revolution and the invincible and iron-willed brilliant commander, as the lodestar of the nation and great man born of Heaven. She devotedly defended the President with the fixed faith that he guarantees the liberation of the country and the prosperity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was an ardent patriot as she dedicated herself to the sacred cause for the country and people with noble patriotic spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 True to the noblest patriotic idea of the President, she always considered her life inseparable from the destiny of the country and did everything for the sake of the country and people in the period of the arduous anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and the building of a new country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was a legendary hero of Mt. Paektu as she performed immortal feats in the struggle for starting and advancing the Songun cause, tightly holding arms of the revolution, the arms of the working class. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Convinced that the liberation of the country and the rosy future of the nation could be brought about only when the Koreans implemented the President's line of armed struggle, the line of attaching importance to arms, she joined the ranks of the anti-Japanese armed struggle with arms in hand and faithfully upheld his cause with arms throughout her revolutionary life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole life of Kim Jong Suk is shining more brilliantly for the undying feats she performed by enabling the Korean nation to be blessed with the illustrious leaders generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest pride and honor for the Korean people to hold Kim Jong Suk in high esteem as the eternal mother of the revolution as her name as the woman commander of Mt. Paektu will be conveyed to posterity along with the august names of the President and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Her idea, spirit, traits and exploits serve as the most precious treasures of eternal value for the Korean revolution and her revolutionary career as a permanent textbook in the life and struggle of the servicepersons and people of the DPRK.

Rodong Sinmun on Kim Jong Suk's Exploits for National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- The whole life of Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero, was a brilliant life dedicated to achieving the sovereignty of the country and the nation and a sacred one as she made an immortal contribution to the patriotic cause of national reunification and great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk devoted her all to implementing President Kim Il Sung's idea and intention to achieve national reunification and performed immortal exploits in that course. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans' cause of reunification started and has developed since its outset, firmly guided by the idea and line of the President. This would be unthinkable without her immortal devotion and efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to her energetic devotion and efforts for national reunification that all the Korean people could unite close around the President irrespective of ideology and ism and the cause of reunification confidently advance from its start, guided by the Juche-oriented idea and line of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What was important among the great exploits performed by her for the cause of national reunification was that she laid a firm foundation for bringing about a bright future of national reunification and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exploit Kim Jong Suk performed by giving birth to and bringing up Kim Jong Il as the sun of the nation who would carve out a bright future of the cause of national reunification will last forever along with the history of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There grew up the dependable second generation of the revolution who would creditably perform the mission and role as the masters responsible for the movement for national reunification. This was the great feat performed by Kim Jong Suk in the history of the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Her noble desire for national reunification is now being translated into a brilliant reality thanks to Kim Jong Il, concludes the article.

U.S. Bellicose Forces' Scenario for Preemptive Attack on DPRK Flayed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Recently the U.S. bellicose forces staged reckless aerial war exercises in a coordinated operation with the U.S. Seventh Air Force present in south Korea while deploying overseas-based F/A-18 and KC-130 and other flying corps in south Korea by turns. The purpose of the exercise was to strike ground targets, provide close air support, fight air battles and make intensive strikes by formations of planes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday terms this saber rattling part of the war moves of the U.S. bellicose forces to stifle the DPRK through surprise attacks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The madcap drills being staged by them to mount a preemptive attack on the DPRK behind the scene of dialogue as part of their preparations for a second Korean war only cast a doubt as to whether the U.S. is willing for dialogue or not, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dialogue advertised by the U.S. while seeking confrontation is, in fact, nothing but a military option to disarm its dialogue partner mentally and mount a surprise preemptive attack on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the intention of the U.S. conservative hard-liners to pressurize the present U.S. administration to call off dialogue with the DPRK and strain the situation in a bid to make it complicated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No one can predict what shocking cases the U.S. bellicose forces will fake up to scuttle the negotiations between the DPRK and the U.S. while busying themselves with war exercises and moves to modernize their armed forces in the future. Their stand is to screw up the military confrontation and ignite a war. This is clearly evidenced by the fact that the U.S. forces are pushing forward such dangerous plan for modernizing their armed forces as the so-called "future combat system" targeted against the DPRK and staging interceptor missile tests one after another. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the U.S. conservative hard-liners are contemplating a reckless preemptive attack on the DPRK, its army and people are making preparations to resolutely counter it. It is the invariable stand and will of the DPRK to respond to dialogue with dialogue and counter force with force.

Japan's Moves to Build up Missile Shield under Fire in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification and the Citizen's Solidarity for Pacifist Constitution in south Korea reportedly made public a joint statement on Dec. 19 denouncing Japan's moves to speed up the building of its missile shield. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that some time ago, a MSDF destroyer shot down a ballistic missile with SM-3 in a test conducted off Hawaii backed by the U.S. Naval Force, the first of its kind, the joint statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is contemplating deploying Aegis ships loaded with SM-3s in surrounding waters of the East Sea of Korea in the future and revising the "guidelines for the use of the missile shield" so that its government may issue an order to intercept missiles at the phase in which "north Korea gets ready to fire missiles." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that the real intention of Japan's buildup of missile shield is to mount a preemptive attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said moves of Japan are intolerable as they diametrically run counter to the moves for establishing a peace-keeping mechanism on the Korean Peninsula, spark an arms race in the surrounding areas and violate its "pacifist constitution" banning the exercise of "the right to collective self-defense." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint statement strongly demanded Japan stop at once the moves to build up the missile shield quite contrary to the peace in Northeast Asia including the Korean Peninsula.

DPRK's Important Days Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Events were held in Russia and Cuba between Dec. 19 and 21 to commemorate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. In Russia a meeting took place under the sponsorship of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK. In Cuba a meeting was held at the Kim Il Sung Economic Special School and a photo exhibition and a film show at Chollima Middle School in Old Havana District,. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the photo exhibition were photos showing the revolutionary history and immortal exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and photos introducing Songun Korea. And the Korean film "The 75th Anniversary of the Heroic Korean People's Army" was appreciated at the film show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kramarenko, vice-chairman of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK, said at the meeting that Kim Jong Il's assumption of the KPA supreme commandership on Dec. 24, 1991, was an event of weighty significance in socialist construction and powerful defence upbuilding in Korea. The revolutionary cause pioneered by President Kim Il Sung will be successfully realized as the Korean army and people are united single-mindedly around Kim Jong Il, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Zhukova, executive manager of the Korean Koryo Medicine Center in Moscow, praised the noble revolutionary career of Kim Jong Suk, woman commander of Mt. Paektu who devotedly defended the headquarters of revolution and gave birth to and brought up Kim Jong Il as brilliant future of Korea, saying that she is a great woman revolutionary who devoted her all to the country and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vorontsov, chief of the Section for Korea of the Institute of Oriental Studies of the Russian Academy of Sciences, said that Kim Jong Il's Songun politics has enervated the U.S. offensive for stifling the DPRK while opening up a bright vista for the Korean people building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Juan Jose Leon Vega, chairman of the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, in his speech at the meeting praised the undying feats performed by the three generals of Mt. Paektu in the sacred cause for the liberation of the country and freedom and happiness of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting in Russia.

Feats of Kim Jong Suk Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 25 (KCNA) -- Edmond Jouve, director-general of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, released a statement on December 17 on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement praised the exploits of Kim Jong Suk who dedicated her all to the emancipation of the Korean women and the development of the women's movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She, whose parents were killed by the Japanese imperialist aggressors, set out on the road of the revolution in her early years and joined the Korean People's Revolutionary Army led by President Kim Il Sung to fight for the liberation of the country with arms in her hands, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest exploit performed by her is that she brought up Kim Jong Il as the successor to Kim Il Sung and as the distinguished leader who would guide the future of Korea, the statement said, adding: She passed away long ago, but her august name and feats will shine forever.

Rodong Sinmun elogia las proezas de Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Las proezas revolucionarias de la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk quedaran conservadas eternamente en el corazon de los militares y habitantes de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un editorial del dia 25 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Jong Suk acumulo las inmortales proezas ante la patria, el pueblo, la epoca y la historia, las cuales son irrealizables para un hombre comun en el transcurso de miles de anos. Y dio brillante ejemplo de la vida y lucha del revolucionario y personal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ella es la indoblegable combatiente revolucionaria quien poseyo la firme concepcion del lider y creo un brillante modelo de la defensa decisiva al lider. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se fio absolutamente del Presidente Kim Il Sung, precursor de la revolucion coreana e invencible y genial comandante de acero, considerandolo como estrella salvadora de la nacion y como hombre legendario. Poseyo una inconmovible conviccion de que solo bajo la orientacion de el es posible lograr la liberacion de la patria y la prosperidad de la nacion y lo defendio a costa de su vida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien, ella es ferviente patriota quien siendo poseedor del noble espiritu patriotico dedico todo lo suyo a la sagrada causa para la patria y el pueblo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estimulada por la noble idea del Presidente Kim Il Sung de amar a la patria, la nacion y el pueblo, ella combino su vida con el destino de la patria e hizo todo lo que estaba a su alcance para la patria y el pueblo en la ardua lucha revolucionaria antijaponesa y la construccion de la nueva patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ella es generala legendaria del monte Paektu quien al tomar firmemente el arma de la revolucion y de la clase realizo inmortales hazanas en la lucha por el allanamiento y progresion de la causa del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A traves de la linea de la lucha armada y de la linea de dar prioridad a las fuerzas armadas presentadas por el Presidente la generala Kim Jong Suk llego a cobrar la fe en la posibilidad de alcanzar la liberacion de la patria y el futuro luminoso de la nacion, se alisto en la fila armada antijaponesa y apoyo fielmente con el fusil la causa del Presidente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La vida de Kim Jong Suk lanza mas brillo por sus inmortales hazanas que permitieron a la nacion coreana tener de generacion en generacion al gran lider y el eminente general. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El nombre de la generala lucira eternamente junto con los nombres del Presidente Kim Il Sung y el Dirigente Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Tenerla como eterna madre de la revolucion deviene la gran gloria y orgullo del pueblo coreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La idea, el espiritu, los rasgos y las proezas de Kim Jong Suk son bienes inestimables de la revolucion coreana y su vida revolucionaria sirve de eterno manual de la vida y lucha del ejercito y el pueblo de Corea.

Actos por efemerides coreanas en Rusia y Cuba
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de diciembre (ATCC) -- En ocasion del 16o aniversario del nombramiento del Dirigente Kim Jong Il como Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea y del 90o aniversario del natalicio de la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk, tuvieron lugar del dia 19 al 21 un mitin en Rusia bajo auspicios de la Asociacion Rusa de Amistad y Cooperacion Cultural con la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, el mismo acto en el Instituto Politecnico de Economia Kim Il Sung de Cuba y la fotoexhibicion y proyeccion filmica en la Escuela Secundaria Chollima en la Habana Vieja de esta nacion antillana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En las galerias fotograficas fueron presentadas las fotos que muestran la historia revolucionaria y las hazanas inmortales de los tres generales del monte Paektu y dan a conocer Corea del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En el encuentro de cine se puso a la pantalla el documental coreano "El 75o aniversario de la fundacion del heroico Ejercito Popular de Corea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El vicepresidente de susodicha asociacion rusa Kramarenko, al hacer uso de la palabra en el mitin, senalo que el nombramiento en el 24 de diciembre de 1991 del Dirigente Kim Jong Il como Comandante Supremo del EPC fue un evento de capital importancia para la construccion del socialismo y de la poderosa defensa nacional de Corea y anadio que gracias a la unidad monolitica del ejercito y el pueblo coreanos en torno al Dirigente, se llevara a su feliz termino la causa revolucionaria iniciada por el Presidente Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La gerente ejecutiva del Centro de Medicina Coryo de Corea en Moscu, Zukova, dijo que la heroina Kim Jong Suk es gran revolucionaria quien dio todo lo suyo por la patria y el pueblo y elogio la noble vida de esta generala del monte Paektu que defendio a costa de la vida a la Comandancia de la Revolucion y dio a luz al excelente sucesor de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El jefe de la seccion coreana del Instituto del Oriente de la Academia de Ciencias de Rusia, Vorontsov, recalco que la politica de Songun del Dirigente hace infructifera la ofensiva de EE.UU. para aplastar a Corea y afirmo que tiene un futuro maravilloso el pueblo coreano que construye una gran potencia prospera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la ocasion fue aprobado un mensaje de felicitacion orientado al Dirigente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@De otro lado, el presidente del Comite Cubano de Apoyo a la Reunificacion de Corea, Juan Jose Leon Vega, en su discurso pronunciado en el mitin, elogio las hazanas inmortales de los 3 generales del monte Paektu acumuladas en la sagrada causa para la liberacion de la patria, la libertad y la felicidad del pueblo.

Cuerpo de Agregados Militares presencia funcion acrobatica
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 16o aniversario del nombramiento del Dirigente Kim Jong Il como Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea y del 90o aniversario del nacimiento de la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk, los miembros del Cuerpo de Agregados Militares en Corea presenciaron el dia 24 una funcion acrobatica conjunta en el Circo del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la escena se pusieron diversas piezas, entre otras, la acrobacia corporal "Burlando la cuerda con bicicleta", la aerea "Habilidad con la goma elastica", la folclorica "Salto sobre el balancin" y el entreacto acrobatico "Jefe de hinchas". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La funcion arranco efusivos aplausos de los espectadores por su alto valor ideo-artistico.
